    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1118603688" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8549412411335290914">Right, well I think the most important concept of the continuation in this story is that the Author reminded us all of his message. That is to love with all your might, cherish all the beautiful memories you create together, learn to give and receive passion to those who deserve your undivided attention and know that there is ALWAYS going to be someone out there that will see you as yourself, YOU will always be somebody&apos;s spark and kryptonite, most of all though he teaches us to never give up ho</span>
  <span id="freeText8549412411335290914" style="display:none">Right, well I think the most important concept of the continuation in this story is that the Author reminded us all of his message. That is to love with all your might, cherish all the beautiful memories you create together, learn to give and receive passion to those who deserve your undivided attention and know that there is ALWAYS going to be someone out there that will see you as yourself, YOU will always be somebody's spark and kryptonite, most of all though he teaches us to never give up hope that this SOMEONE is out there waiting for you to find them, heal them, and just LOVE them.<br /><br />Although I love all the characters in this unique, creative tease of a series, there will no way ever be another like SCRIBER. Sorry RUIN, I do love you but... I'm a fickle book boyfriend cheater-a-holic! =) Also I must say, Sam is a new character I'm going to look forward to meeting again and again, she might even make me want to "change teams" lol<br /><br />Thank You for something new Lucian Bane. I shall forgive you for being naughty to my baby RUIN.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8549412411335290914" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


