<div id="review_1869649991" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1869649991" />
    <a title="JoJo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54221183-jojo"><img alt="JoJo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1458803178p2/54221183.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1869649991?book_show_action=true">Jan 07, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="JoJo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="JoJo" href="/user/show/54221183-jojo">JoJo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/54221183-jojo?shelf=twisted-love">twisted-love</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1869649991" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1589398377792476736">First, love Bane. His writing style, imagination &amp; development mannerisms. <br/>The paranormal style is not my usual taste. <br/>Religious stuff is definitely not my taste. EVER. <br/>He&apos;s a very devoted Christian. <br/>I&apos;m just a so-so Christian with serious God issues, but I respect his writing &amp; the fact he incorporates his values &amp; knowledge into his stories....even though I don&apos;t want to read anything about the God stuff, I want to read Banes stuff. It just makes it hard at times. Makes for a lot of interestin</span>
  <span id="freeText1589398377792476736" style="display:none">First, love Bane. His writing style, imagination &amp; development mannerisms. <br>The paranormal style is not my usual taste. <br>Religious stuff is definitely not my taste. EVER. <br>He's a very devoted Christian. <br>I'm just a so-so Christian with serious God issues, but I respect his writing &amp; the fact he incorporates his values &amp; knowledge into his stories....even though I don't want to read anything about the God stuff, I want to read Banes stuff. It just makes it hard at times. Makes for a lot of interesting inner dialogue to say the least lol<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1483883730ra/21658503.gif" width="350px" height="250px" alt="" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I recommend this series 100% with 5 ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ if you're into the God stuff mixed with paranormal sex/romance. It's that good &amp; deep. As usual with his perfect style, this book covers everything you need. Everything. <br><br>Personal thoughts.....<br><br>For me &amp; my personal taste, this portion was where it sunk. I had a hard time here. I had a hard time even getting into this type of book. I'm onboard 100% with dark erotica or erotica. It's my thing right now. <br>But mixing the two...it's why I stopped reading the Claw series 1/2 way through. <br><br>Here, I stuck it out. Something about the way Ruin was written &amp; developing. Izzy too. It evolved more towards a love &amp; life story, so I was able to wrap my head around it &amp; I did get fully invested in these two. How 3 ended hurt. And how this 4th one went...it's just off. Ruin didn't know any of this sex stuff till Izzy &amp; to be realistic, how fast can that heat happen again after a tragedy? It seemed too fast here, like 48 or 72 hours??? It seemed rushed. I get he's "different" so the usual may not apply, but it still seemed way rushed. No build, but I don't want this direction for Ruin so even if there was a slow build I'd still probably find fault. <br><br>And Sam? In the last few moments of the book completely did a 180 in 0.4 seconds &amp; the worse part? So did Ruin...so I'm supposed to be all right there with them too? Nah. I'll pass. No Bueno bro.<br><br><br>And still no closer to any answers. Even after re-reading this &amp; the 3rd, I seriously got lost. I'm missing some key parts that confused the fuck out of me so I'm not sure if it only seems to me that it's jumping over parts, leaving gaps to jump to a new fraction of story line, or did it really do that? I'm sure me not catching on is because of my lack of knowledge of this subject. But I'm craving answers, I'll admit that. <br><br>This is now the fourth series by various people that I've started, got book ass deep....then nothing. Now I have to add this to the "watch for the next" list....I hate my lack of patients. <br><br>For now....this is me. Once again. Waiting. <br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1483071619ra/21576478.gif" width="350pk" height="250px" alt="" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="1589398377792476736" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


